{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Menu Item Active State Highlighting\n\nResolve the issue where visited or currently active menu items are not displaying the correct visual highlight indicator.\n\nRequirements:\n- Identify the current routing or navigation state management system\n- Ensure active menu items receive the appropriate CSS class or styling\n- Verify the highlight appears immediately when navigating to a route\n- Maintain highlight persistence when page refreshes on an active route\n- Handle edge cases:\n  - Nested routes should highlight both parent and child menu items\n  - Query parameters should not affect active state matching\n  - Trailing slashes in URLs should be handled consistently\n- Test across all menu items to ensure consistent behavior\n- Verify highlight is removed from previously active items when navigating away",
  "title": "Fix active menu item highlighting across routes",
